    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/3759¾</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">27 March, 1917</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: It is clear to me that the only
                    thing we can prudently do is to urge both Cuba and Panama to do just what we
                    do.</p>
                <p>In case Cuba follows our lead it will be necessary, I take it for granted, to
                    give her our military protection as fully as we give it to Porto Rico and St.
                    Thomas. I hope that you will get the negotiations in course as soon as possible,
                    but that you will first confer with Baker and Daniels about the practical
                    consequences and our ability to handle them.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
